1.2.1.6c Continue training and skilling tax officers to match the technical requirements of the industries MoFPED
1.2.1.6d Continue supporting the businesspeople and investors to creat more wealth and get more people out of the 68% in agriculture subsistence sector MoFPED
1.2.1.6e This Manifesto has been developed without oil revenue inflows in consideration. When the first oil revenue expected in 2023 comes in, we shall be able to do more MoFPED
1.2.1.7 Expenditure Control Measures 1.2.1.7a Rationalisation of money-consuming agencies and restructuring government to eliminate 'agencification'  of government and duplication MoPS
1.2.1.7b Restructure the national budget and ensure that all consumptive items in the development budget are shifted to the non-wage budget for better monitoring and control against wastage. MoFPED
1.2.1.7c Implementation of pay reforms for civil servants to improve implementation discipline. MoPS
1.2.1.7d Implementation of a programme-based budget in line with the NDP III programmatic approach, whose alignment  with the national budget allocations and other strategic priorities  is no longer negotiable MoFPED
1.2.1.7e Renegotiate with our development partners to ensure that funds for ongoing projects that were allocated on consumptive expenditure are re-channelled to the NDP III priorities within the respective sectors. MoFPED
1.2.1.7f Addressing  issues that have been impeding project implementation, particularly procurement-related constraints and land acquisition to give right of way for the construction  of roads and power lines. MoLHUD
